You may include a stack of these and encourage your client to take some home, so she can continue to document this important event in her life. Providing this resource helps your client to overcome the secrecy surrounding this important aspect of her life.

After Abortion Support Journal 'N'AR Prise

This notebook is for women to write down their feelings regarding their abortion. As many women rarely talk about their abortions, this notebook provides them with an alternative space to document their experience.

Siné In Dukola Guésen

Guénsal translates to ‘Name of God’. This journal is for women to write down prayers to God. It is used as a form of catharsis and helps the client to increase hope. This notebook provides a gift should the client have a completed counselling session.

Private Prayer Booklet for Epileptic Women by Seveti Songay Maty Ndiaye

Not every society views Epilepsy in the same way. This booklet gives real life testimonies of fellow Senegalese women who have epilepsy. This source of support and reassurance helps women with epilepsy to feel understood and hopeful about their future.
